  "text": "If more than two targets are presented in a row, however, a number of studies have shown that subjects are capable of reporting these targets without showing an AB [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . It seems as if Lag 1 sparing can be extended to more than two targets and longer time periods (see also [CITATION_4] . The current version of the ST 2 model cannot account for spreading the sparing; for work on a revised version of the model that addresses these findings please refer to Wyble et al. (in press ).",
